name: DESA WISATA PINGE
address: J55H+VJF, Pinge Baru, Kec. Marga, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82181, Indonesia
review 1:
My uncle's village. This village is still quiet, the weather is quite cold, the modern touch is very minimal so that the authentic Balinese feel is still felt.
The access is indeed narrow, but still accessible by car and bus.
Accommodation is available in the form of a home stay that mingles with residents in the village.
You have to contact the village administrator to invite guests on vacation there.
review 2: Very nice and clean village and even they open home stay for everyone to experience live with local people. Today is our 1st day trip and we are in Desa Wisata Pinge
review 3: One of the best tourism village. Good nature, good people, good food. Recommended.
review 4: Quiet, not busy, relaxed little village.
review 5: Nice,clean and quiet village at Desa Baru Tabanan. There are some home stay for travelers to stay in a traditional vilage like Pinge. One may involve or join some activities during staying at Pinge. Enjoy other style of vacation, learn and discover more about the local's life based on "tourism based local community".

name: Pinge Traditional Village And Homestay
address: Jl. Banjar Pinge, Tua, Kec. Marga, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82191, Indonesia
review 1: It's a picturesque place - beautiful & feel magical. It's quite, relax and quite traditional. Able to stay in typical trafitional Balinese house compound - which everything is build separately : kitchen, bedrooms, bathrooms all are in separate buildings. Quite big verandah, where we used as dining place, sitting on the floor/carpet.
review 2: You may see rice field, coconut tree and such a clean environment but it offers you to do many thing from learn how to make traditional balinese cake with natural ingredients, learn balinese dance, join farmer in the rice field, live and learn the traditional balinese in local guest house and home stay, etc. The location is near with Jatiluwih, Angseri hotspring, Bedugul Botanical Garden, Ulun Danu temple.
review 3: the best one in bali and please visit this village
